description:
Are you motivated by challenges, variety, and learning? If you are a young professional who wants to start a career in IT, we have the right position for you! We are hiring a Junior Project Management Officer to join our project team in Munich. You will report directly to the project manager and support various projects with varying degrees of complexity. You are the business key contact and act as an interface between business and IT.

What Will You Do

– Supporting the Project Manager in managing projects, including stakeholder relationships and deliverables time, cost, and quality requirements;

– Participate in cross-functional working group sessions to translate business requirements into system specifications;

– Assist with the functional documentation of customer business requirements;

– Support user acceptance testing and address investigation of questions, issues, and defects;

– Managing the expectations and satisfaction of clients, project sponsors, and stakeholders.

What Will Help You To Fulfill Your Role

– A university degree in an analytical field e.g., Economics, Engineering, Business, Finance, or related fields;

– Exceptional analytical and problem-solving skills;

– Ability to work effectively with management and be part of a team to meet targets;

– Ability to influence stakeholders and work closely with them to determine acceptable solutions;

– Strong attention to detail;

– Good communication skills, both written and verbal;

– Business proficiency in English and German is a must. Proficiency in Italian is desired.

What We Offer

– A multitude of demanding projects in an international context;


 * Transparent career program;



– Professional in-house training programs, including on-the-job, constructive feedback, and coaching;

– A flat hierarchy, which will not be tied up in politics;

– Autonomy in your day-to-day processes.

– Access to company benefits programs, including discounts and VIP memberships;


 * Drinks and snacks in our offices;



START

ASAP

EMPLOYMENT TYPE

Full-Time / Part-Time

INDUSTRY

Information Technology, Financial Services

LOCATION

Munich (Germany)

CONTACT

Francesco di Cugno

Convolut GmbH | Radlkoferstr 2 | 81373 München

tel: (+49) (0) 89 80035334

E-Mail: career@convolut.eu

The ideal candidate will be responsible for planning, coordinating, and implementing projects within the decided-upon budget, timeline, and scope. They will also effectively monitor and present project updates to relevant stakeholders, clients, or project team members.



Responsibilities

 * Responsible for coordinating the bidding technical solution design of offshore wind power projects, organizing and coordinating professional resources to communicate and carry out design with owners and design institutes, etc., and promoting the implementation of projects;
 * Responsible for cooperating with the operation team to track, sort out and analyze the regional planning, policies and development trends of the offshore wind power market, and exploring market opportunities;
 * Responsible for coordinating sales team to support key offshore wind power projects, and develop competitive offshore wind power lifecycle products and technical solutions.




Qualifications




 * Master degree or above. Major in Wind Energy, Fluid Dynamics, Energy and Power, is preferred.
 * Have the ability of resource evaluation analysis and overall solution design;
 * Familiar with wind resource evaluation and analysis software such as Windographer, WT, WAsP, WindSim, WindPro, etc., have programming ability and can process and analyze relevant data;
 * Have strong learning ability, can quickly accept and understand the industry knowledge and the latest cutting-edge technology, development trends;
 * Have strong ability of internal and external communication and coordination skills, as well as teamwork.

cultivation pattern

 * Take a series of training for 6 - 12-month at the headquarter (in Zhongshan, Guangdong, China), then will go back to Europe.
 * Subsequently return to the headquarter for some training and communication as needed.
